cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use CLAIR (Cascaded Lazy AI Routing) in your research or products,
  please cite it using the metadata below.
type: software
title: "CLAIR — Cascaded Lazy AI Routing"
abstract: >-
  CLAIR is a composable architecture for reducing token consumption and improving
  capability discovery in LLM-based agent systems. It introduces a lightweight
  always-on router (~280 tokens) that lazily loads domain-specific skill documents
  and MCP tools only when they are relevant to the active task, and provides an
  ML-offload routing layer that directs repetitive subtasks to efficient non-LLM
  backends. A controlled A/B test demonstrated 72.6% average token reduction
  (9,930 → 2,719 tokens per request) across 7 task categories including travel
  planning, UI development, debugging, and API development.
